Greg M. Cooper/USA TODAY SportsCarmelo Anthony and the Knicks might be playoff-bound, but they really aren't that good. Call it Newton's law of "emotion:" For every player and team that flies under the radar, there must be another that is generating entirely too much hype. After my Per Diem partner Tom Haberstroh took a look at the NBA's most underrated yesterday, today I get the task of looking at the league's most overrated, including a pair of teams who will be showcased on TNT tonight. Most overrated Eastern Conference team: New York Knicks I've written at length about why SCHOENE is so down on the Knicks. In reality, the 37-45 projection is something of a worst-case scenario for New York. I'm expecting something like 45 wins -- which would still be a drop of nine from last year's total of 54. There's actually plenty of precedent for that kind of slide. To read more of Kevin Pelton's Most Overrated list, become an Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Kevin Pelton Follow Archive Co-author, Pro Basketball Prospectus series Formerly a consultant with the Indiana Pacers Developed WARP rating and SCHOENE system